The poorest attendance to greet the Dodgers for an opening game, despite the good weather. Promoter Jack Dempsey was present, seated behind the Dodger bench, and he received an ovation from the fans who were quick to recognize the former boxing champion.

It appeared Elliott swung at a 3rd strike but Ump Rigler called it a ball.  A grand old powwow ensued.  Maranville came in from short to argue it out.  Taylor hurled down his mask and let the ball go with it.  Cullop tried to take advantage but Taylor recovered and flipped to Maranville at home.
$Braves: bases loaded, 1 out when game called due to rain. Singles by Maguire and Sisler, plus a walk to Harper, were washed off the books.
